&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within this dynamic team. If you like to be busy, enjoy a good team atmosphere and enjoy the challenge of working in the Emergency Department then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit staff nurses who are keen to develop their career in emergency nursing, working alongside our Clinical Educator to complete your personal competency development package. Successful candidates will be expected to deliver excellence in patient centred quality care and contribute to the improvement of service provision. We will consider newly qualified and experienced nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post involves, weekday, weekend and night duty rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full time post working 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alice Dudley Senior Sister on Tel: 01872253110 or email alice.dudley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
